  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Validate a simple and cost-effective Nucleic Acid Test for HIV Detection in order to develop
      a rapid, highly sensitive and specific, one-stage test for the diagnosis of HIV infection.
      Blood samples collected will be assayed using the BioHelix Corporation helicase-dependent
      amplification or the Cepheid Xpert HIV-1 Quant Assay. A false negative or false positive rate
      of &gt;1.0% would make this test unacceptable as a screening test for HIV viremia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
